Task 5: Requirements for UserFormPage and UserDisplayPage
1.	UserFormPage (User Input Page)
Purpose: Allows users to enter and save their email, phone number, and status.
Requirements:
•	Input Fields: 
o	Text field for email input.
o	Text field for phone number input.
o	Radio buttons to select user status (Active/Deactive).
•	Button: 
o	"Submit" button to save the entered data.
•	Local Storage: 
o	Uses SharedPreferences to store user details persistently.
•	Validation: 
o	Ensure valid email format.
o	Ensure phone number contains only digits and has a valid length.
o	Status selection is mandatory.
2.	UserDisplayPage (User Data Display Page)
Purpose: Displays the stored user information in a structured format.
Requirements:
•	Data Presentation: 
o	Uses a DataTable to display email, phone number, and status.
o	Status Icon: 
	Green ✅ (checkmark) for Active.
	Red ❌ (cross) for Deactive.
•	Data Retrieval: 
o	Fetches user data from SharedPreferences.
•	Error Handling: 
o	Includes mounted checks to prevent errors while retrieving data.
Summary:
•	UserFormPage → Input and save user details.
•	UserDisplayPage → Retrieve and display user details.
•	Data is stored locally using SharedPreferences for persistence.
